[b]Smooth Trend Radar[/b]

[b]What it does[/b]
Takes the Supertrend indicator further: instead of using the bands directly for a binary signal, this script averages the upper and lower Supertrend bands into a midline and applies a double smoothing pass (WMA followed by EMA). The result is a baseline that changes direction far less frequently than standard Supertrend — trend is determined by whether the baseline is rising or falling, not by price crossing the bands. On top of the baseline, the script adds pivot-based rejection signals, statistical overextension highlighting via candle coloring, and full SL/TP visualization on every trend flip.

[b]Features[/b]
[list]
[*][b]Double-smoothed baseline[/b] — Supertrend bands averaged, then WMA → EMA smoothed. Significantly fewer whipsaws than standard Supertrend
[*][b]Auto Timeframe Scaling[/b] — Supertrend factor, ATR period, smoothing lengths, pivot window, and overextension threshold all auto-adjust per chart timeframe (1m → W). Manual inputs remain as fallback
[*][b]Slope-based trend[/b] — bullish when baseline rises, bearish when it falls
[*][b]Pivot-based rejection[/b] — confirmed swing low/high at the baseline, validated by sustained baseline contact and a slope filter. One signal per actual extremum, no clustering
[*][b]Statistical overextension[/b] — bars where the distance from baseline ranks in the top X% of the lookback window are highlighted with accent candle coloring (purple = far below baseline, orange = far above). Self-adapts to symbol and timeframe — no multiplier tuning needed
[*][b]SL / TP setup[/b] — on every trend flip (or rejection re-entry), entry, SL, and three TP levels are drawn with extended horizontal lines, labels, and risk/reward fills. Three SL methods (Flip Candle / Baseline / Swing) and four TP modes (Pivot R/S / R-Multiple / Fibonacci / ATR)
[*][b]Re-Entry on Rejection[/b] — after an SL hit with unchanged trend, the next confirmed rejection signal rebuilds the setup at current price
[*][b]Trail to Break-Even[/b] — optional: when TP1 is hit, SL moves to entry. Trade can no longer result in a loss
[*][b]Hover tooltips[/b] — every flip and rejection label shows price, direction, and timestamp on hover
[*][b]Direction-aware alerts[/b] — for flips, rejections, TP hits, and SL hits
[/list]

[b]How to read it[/b]
[list]
[*][b]Baseline color[/b] — green = uptrend, red = downtrend
[*][b]▲ / ▼ on baseline[/b] — trend flip, the entry trigger
[*][b]Small ▲ / ▼ at price[/b] — rejection at a confirmed pivot near the baseline
[*][b]Purple candle[/b] — bull-side overextension: price is statistically far below the baseline. Potential reversal up
[*][b]Orange candle[/b] — bear-side overextension: price is statistically far above the baseline. Potential reversal down
[*][b]Horizontal lines[/b] — current SL and TP1/TP2/TP3 levels
[*][b]Red zone[/b] — risk between entry and SL
[*][b]Green zone[/b] — reward between entry and TP3
[/list]

[b]Settings to tune[/b]
[list]
[*][b]Auto Timeframe Scaling[/b] (default on) overrides the smoothing parameters with timeframe-appropriate defaults. Disable to use the manual inputs
[*][b]Min Baseline Touches[/b] and [b]Slope Lookback[/b] control how strict the rejection filter is — higher values = fewer but cleaner signals
[*][b]Overextension Lookback / Percentile Threshold[/b] — lookback how far back to compare distances; threshold controls how extreme a bar must be before it is flagged. Default 100 bars / top 15%
[*][b]TP Method[/b] — switch between Pivot R/S levels, R-Multiples, Fibonacci extensions, or ATR multiples
[*][b]SL Method[/b] — Flip Candle, Baseline, or Swing structure
[/list]

